Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, Jan. 10 KYODO -- The special committee on 
political reform of the House of Councillors voted Monday [10 
January] to set a public hearing for government-proposed 
political reform bills for January 17. 
  A bill can be put to the vote at a Diet committee after the 
public hearing is concluded. 
  The four political reform bills that Prime Minister Morihiro 
Hosokawa has vowed to enact during the current Diet session, 
which ends January 29, are pending before the upper house after 
being passed by the House of Representatives in mid-November. 

